<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,405,783,808]" italics="true" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Eragrostis polytricha</emphasis>
Nees
</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[166,779,822,1506]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,330,822,846]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Identification.</emphasis>
Perennial tussock grass, 
<quantity box="[596,699,823,847]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.75" metricValueMax="7.5" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="47.5" valueMax="75.0" valueMin="20.0">20–75 cm</quantity>
height. Leaf-blades linear, without glandules, trichomes densely present on both sides, 
<quantity box="[412,507,890,914]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.8" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="18.5" valueMax="28.0" valueMin="9.0">9–28 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[576,711,890,914]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.65" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="2.3" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="0.365" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.23">0.23–0.5 cm</quantity>
wide, ligulate. It is identified by its open panicle, 
<quantity box="[669,779,923,947]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.2" metricValueMax="2.9" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="22.0" valueMax="29.0" valueMin="15.0">15–29 cm</quantity>
long, 
<quantity box="[231,339,957,981]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.3" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" unit="cm" value="18.5" valueMax="23.0" valueMin="14.0">14–23 cm</quantity>
wide, with trichomes present along the main axis and at the axils.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[168,510,1029,1054]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="24.[166,779,822,1506]" box="[168,510,1029,1054]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,349,1029,1054]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Common name.</emphasis>
Palha-voadora
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="24" pageNumber="531" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="24.[166,779,822,1506]" box="[168,745,1068,1093]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,279,1068,1092]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Remarks.</emphasis>
A common species at the native grassland.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="24.[166,779,822,1506]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[168,357,1107,1131]" pageId="24" pageNumber="531">Brazilian range.</emphasis>
Midwest, North (RR state), Northeast (BA, PB and PE states), South and Southeast (except RJ state) regions.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
